ect. Deploy Apr 13 with V6 cooldown.\n\n**Next:** P2 smart entry\n\n---\n## 2026-04-02 12:41 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Full Morning Session: 7 trades, 5W/2L = 71% WR\n\n**Task:** P4 alpha research \u2014 analyze full 11-12h session, explain why YES wins in falling BTC, forecast 19h\n\n**Apr 2 Session Update: 7 trades (was 6 at last check), 5W/2L = 71% WR**\n- 11h: 6 trades (4W/2L = 67%)\n- 12h: 1 trade (1W/0L = 100%) \u2014 biggest move of session (BTC $65,964\u2192$66,134 = +$170)\n- All 7 trades V5a PASS. V5a shadow: 69 windows collected (target 30 \u2705).\n- CLOB balance: $902.80 (likely +$20 unredeemed)\n\n**KEY INSIGHT: Contrarian YES Wins in Falling Markets (RANGE Regime)**\n- BTC fell $66,380\u2192$65,964 during session (-0.6%)\n- But 5-min candles MEAN-REVERT within each window\n- Crowd bets NO (BTC will drop) \u2192 negative bias \u2192 our contrarian buys YES\n- 5/7 micro-bounces happened even as macro trend was down\n- Losses were small moves (-$40 BTC). Wins caught the rebounds.\n- **This is WHY RANGE regime filter is critical** \u2014 mean-reversion only works in RANGE, not TREND.\n\n**19h Session Forecast:**\n- BTC $66,208, still drifting lower. Regime:",
